data.content:
Created both files. Here's what the component does:

- **Generic** — `@typeparam TItem` makes it work with any type.
- **Internal copy** — `OnParametersSet` copies `Items` into `_items`, so the caller's list is never mutated.
- **Move Up / Move Down** — tuple-swap the adjacent items, then fire `OnOrderChanged` with a read-only snapshot.
- **Buttons auto-disable** — "Move Up" is disabled on the first item, "Move Down" on the last.

**Usage** (matches your example):

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<MyTask> tasks = new() { ... };

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<MyTask> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
